{"title":"fix(remediation): remove invalid nodeSelector from vigil-app Deployment","body":"Root cause: Deployment vigil-app specifies nodeSelector for non-existent node 'nonexistent-bogus-node', causing pods to remain Pending as no matching nodes exist in the cluster.

Evidence: Warning FailedScheduling 0/3 nodes are available: 3 node(s) didn't match Pod's node affinity/selector.

Fix: Remove the invalid nodeSelector from the Deployment spec to allow scheduling on available nodes."}
